#: admin/page-help.php:15
msgid "Frequently Asked Questions"
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:20
msgid "Do I need to create a backup before using this plugin?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:23
msgid "Yes — always create a full database backup before deleting any post meta data. Deletions are permanent and cannot be undone without a backup."
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:24
msgid "You can create a backup using a backup plugin (e.g. UpdraftPlus, All-in-One WP Migration) or directly from phpMyAdmin by exporting your database."
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:31
msgid "Can a deletion be undone?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:34
msgid "No. Deletions are irreversible and can only be restored from a database backup."
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:41
msgid "The operation is very slow or seems to be stuck — what should I do?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:44
msgid "The plugin processes posts in batches. If the operation is slow or appears to hang, reduce the batch size in the Settings page."
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:45
msgid "Lower the \"Process Speed\" value (e.g. from 50 to 10–20). This reduces the number of posts processed per request, which lowers the load on your server."
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:52
msgid "What is the difference between \"Delete (key + value)\" and \"Delete (value only)\"?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:56
msgid "Delete (key + value):"
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:58
msgid "Permanently removes the meta key and all its values from every post. The key will no longer appear in the table."
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:61
msgid "Delete (value only):"
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:63
msgid "Clears the stored value but keeps the meta key in the database. The key remains visible in the table with a count of 0."
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:70
msgid "What does the \"Count\" column show?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:73
msgid "The Count column shows the number of posts that have a non-empty value stored for the given meta key. Posts that have the key but an empty value are not counted."
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:80
msgid "What are the Edit actions (Overwrite, Search and replace)?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:86
msgid "Replaces the full post meta field content for all posts with the new value you enter. Use this when you want to set the same value everywhere."
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:91
msgid "Finds and replaces text only in the stored values. Array keys (names) in serialized data remain unchanged. Works on both plain text and serialized arrays."
msgstr ""

#: admin/page-help.php:96
msgid "Finds and replaces text in both values and array keys within serialized data. Use this when you need to rename keys (e.g. pa_color to pa_color2) in addition to values."
msgstr ""

